description:
Bug 38131: ajc needs -d option. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce:
1. Create a class in a subpackage:
   package subpackage;
   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }
2. Compile using the following command: ajc subpackage\Test.java

Observed Behavior:
- The Test.class file is then put in subpackage\subpackage directory.
- Running the java command results in the following exception:
   Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: subpackage/Test

Expected Behavior:
- Running either of the following commands should fix the problem: ajc -d . or ajc -d subpackage subpackage\Test.java
